Name: Whitman Coin Folders
Description: Whitman folders open flat for all-at-once viewing and includes data pertaining to the coins it holds.

Name: Harris Coin Folders
Description: H. E. Harris coin folders are great for organizing coin collections. Harris folders are economical and easy to use and available for most modern US coins.

Name: Dansco Replacement Pages
Description: These replacement pages are made by Dansco and will fit any Dansco coin album. With the exception of the vinyl pages, these pages are rigid and feature clear acetate sheets on the front and back that sandwich coins in place. All of the pages are archival safe and will keep your coins safe for years.

Name: Slip Cases
Description:
The Dansco Archival Quality Slipcase has been produced with Silver-Guard Corrosion-Inhibiting protection. No other product on the Market matches Silver-Guard Corrosion-Inhibiting protection against corrosion. This Military Specification material permanently neutralizes corrosive gases in the air that can cause toning and discoloring. This works with silver, gold, copper and nickel coins and medals, medallions, bars and ferrous metals.

Dansco Coin Albums have always been made with the best archival materials and now with the addition of this finely crafted slipcase, the protection is invaluable. The slipcase will not remove existing toning. Always handle your coins properly. It is best to store your coins in a cool, dry place and away from extreme temperature or humidity changes.

Name: Album Binders
Description: Dansco Coin Binders are sold without any pages or slides. You are able to make a custom album starting with the binders.

Name: Millimeter Pages
Description: We offer a variety of MM sized Dansco Album pages from 16mm through 70mm. These pages fit into Dansco Albums.

Name: Tubes
Description: Coin tubes provide a great way to organize and store your collection while keeping it safe from contamination unprotected coins can encounter. A long time staple of numismatics, coin collecting tubes are widely used because they are a safe and convenient way to store coins. We offer both the round and square types of coin tubes.

Name: Folders
Description: Coin Folders are the most economical way to organize a coin collection.  These are perfect for both starting coin collectors and experienced collectors.

Name: Whitman
Description: The highest standards and quality go into the manufacturing process to create a finished product that protects your coins. As you build your unique collection, Whitman is there to provide an archival environment that you will be pleased with for years to come.

Name: Dansco Coin Folders
Description:
Bound in simulated leather, beautifully gold stamped to furnish a truly luxurious setting for your coin collection. Ports are the exact size of the coin, holding the coin securely by friction. Ports are inscribed with the year, mint and number of coins minted.

These all in one coin folder are of a lie flat construction making it easy to insert the coins into the ports. It opens out to allow inspection or display of your coins from beginning to end without having to turn pages

Name: Susan B. Anthony/Sacagawea Small Dollar Holders
Hansen Plastics American Silver Eagle Holders
Holders & Displays
Description:
Plastic coin holders offer a wide variety of protection and display options for your collection. Plastic coin holders protect your collection from the wear and tear of handling as well as from oils and other substances coming in contact with the surface of the coins.

Each plastic coin holder features a clear window for easy viewing of each side of your coin. There are a variety of sizes and backgrounds that will enhance the presentation of your coins.

Name: Storage
Description: Proper coin storage is absolutely essential to maintaining the value of a coin collection. If improperly stored, an increased chance of mishandling, corrosion or contamination may occur and the value of a once-great collection could be lost forever.

Name: Dansco
Description:
What is a Dansco Coin Album?

Dansco coin albums are the most popular coin album that we sell and are available for practically any collection that you can conceive including foreign coins. One of the most outstanding features is the consistent quality of Dansco Coin products which means that we rarely have any quality issues. Dansco coin albums are made with interchangeable parts that allow your collections to grow and make it easy for you to replace pages if needed.

Dansco Album Components

The Binder – Simulated leather embossed and beautifully foil stamped. The inside covers of most albums contain a historical overview of the collection and mintage figures for each production hear. The center column is permanently riveted to the exterior binder and holds the pages in place by way of two metal post screws/nuts, which make page replacement easy for anyone.
The Pages – Loose-leaf hinged pages that are plastic coated and washable. Each page has coin ports that hold coins between acetate slides that both protect and display both sides of your collection. Most pages are imprinted with identifying information including mint mark (when applicable) and mint years. Adding coins to your Dansco coin album is as simple as pushing the top slide to the right edge of the page, inserting your coin and sliding the acetate sheet back in place.

Name: Albums
Description:
Coin Albums allow you to organize, view & protect your coin collection. 


Most coin series are available in the following album formats: 

Date Set - Albums that hold one coin per mint year
P&D Set - Albums that hold one Philadelphia and one Denver Mint coin per mint year
Proof Set - Albums that hold P&D coins plus a proof from the San Francisco Mint
(note: Dansco proof sets usually also hold a Silver Proof)
 
We offer:

Individual Coin Albums: These albums hold coins safely behind protective layers.

Slab Albums: These albums hold PCGS & NGC coin slabs.

Coin Wallets: These albums hold coins already enclosed in protective flips.

Currency Albums: These albums hold currency notes.
